WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:12.624
Of the four ways the dashboard can tell you to trade this
setup, this is the aggressive one. Fastest Growth. Let's
see what it actually does, and exactly who it's for.

2
00:00:13.224 --> 00:00:25.920
It's the first recommendation card, in Step two. Fastest
Growth bets the most of your edge. In betting-math terms,
close to full Kelly, which is the mathematical maximum
before you're actually over-betting and hurting yourself.

3
00:00:26.520 --> 00:00:39.864
Its entire job is speed. On a prop account, it finds the
setup and the size that reaches the profit target in the
fewest days. On your own money, the most expected dollar
growth. Notice it picks the biggest position size of the
four cards.

4
00:00:40.464 --> 00:00:54.480
But speed always has a price. Look at the pass and bust
bar on this card. It's the highest bust rate of the four.
Full-Kelly sizing means the deepest drawdowns and the
wildest swings. You grow the fastest, but you also blow up
the most often.

5
00:00:55.080 --> 00:01:06.576
So who is this actually for? Aggressive traders in a
growth phase, on cheap accounts they can afford to re-buy
if a streak busts them. If a blown account is a real
problem for you, this is simply not your card.

6
00:01:07.176 --> 00:01:14.208
Fastest Growth. Maximum speed, maximum variance. The right
pick only when you can genuinely afford to lose the bet.
